@@YACK!MUD TNG — Staff Conduct@@N

As a staff member on ACK!TNG you are staff, not a player.  The same three
rules that govern players apply to you — and then some.  Players see you
as a representative of the game.  Act accordingly.

@@RDON'T:@@N

  a) KILL, HARM, or HARASS PLAYERS — this includes:
       - Changing titles, stats, sex, or class without consent
       - Using SWITCH, FORCE, or spells against players
       - Misusing channels (emote, say, gossip, echo) to belittle players
       - Being deliberately unhelpful or condescending

  b) GIVE UNFAIR ADVANTAGES — this includes:
       - Using OLOAD or MLOAD to give players equipment or easy kills
       - Using MSET or OSET to enhance items or weaken mobs for players
       - Handing out gold, exp, or items outside of sanctioned events

  c) ACT ON PERSONAL BIAS — treat all players equally.  The moment you
     start helping friends and ignoring strangers, you have failed at
     the job.

@@GSHOULD:@@N

  a) BE HELPFUL.  If you are online and not building, you are available.
     A player asking a genuine question deserves a genuine answer.

  b) BE FAIR.  Apply rules and consequences consistently.  No favorites.

  c) USE FREEZE SPARINGLY.  It is a last resort, not an expression of
     frustration.  Prefer DENY or NUKE for serious violations after
     consulting with senior staff.

  d) LOG ACTIONS.  Nearly everything you do is logged.  Behave as though
     every command will be reviewed.

@@RIMPORTANT:@@N

  Staff status on ACK!TNG is not a reward.  It is a responsibility.
  Abuse it and it will be removed.  Repeated violations will result in
  deletion.  No warnings, no appeals.

  See also:  @@cHELP RULES@@N
